metadata.content:
# Gobi Glie - Behind the scenes[]

Gobi Glie first appeared in "Liberty on Ryloth," the twenty-first episode of the first season of the television series Star Wars: The Clone Wars. The episode, which was written by Henry Gilroy and directed by Rob Coleman, first aired on March 13, 2009. In the brief appearance, Glie was voiced by Corey Burton, who reprised the character in the third episode of season three, "Supply Lines," where Gobi has an expanded role.

Glie later appeared in the second season of Star Wars Rebels, "Homecoming," which aired on February 26, 2016, and is featured again in the season three episode "Hera's Heroes." Unlike his previous appearances, Glie is a prominent character in a two-episode story arc of the series Star Wars: The Bad Batch, in the episodes "Devil's Deal" and "Rescue on Ryloth," which premiered on Disney+ on July 9 and July 16, 2021, respectively. Burton voiced Glie once again in both Rebels and The Bad Batch.
